Harira
  --America's Test Kitchen

1/3 c  evoo
1 onion, diced
2 celery ribs, diced
1 tbsp fresh ginger
5 cloves garlic, minced
2 tsp smoked paprika
2 tsp ground coriander
1 tsp ground cumin
1/2 tsp cinnamon
1/8 tsp pepper flakes
3/4 c minced cilantro, divided
1/2 c minced parsley, divided
4 c chicken broth
4 c water
15 oz can chickpeas, drained and rinsed
1 c brown lentils, rinsed and picked through
20 oz can crushed tomatoes
1/2 c orzo
4 oz swiss chard leaves cut into 1/2" pieces
2 tbsp lemon juice

Heat oil over medium high heat in dutch oven. When it starts shimmering, add onion and celery and cook until translucent and slightly browned, ~7 min. Add ginger and garlic, let cook until fragrant, ~1 min. Add paprika, coriander, cumin, cinnamon, and pepper flakes, and cook, stirring constantly, for ~1 min. Add 1/2 c cilantro and 1/4 c parsley, stir, cook for 1 min more. Add water and broth, stir to scrape up fond. Add chickpeas and lentils,  turn heat up to medium high until it comes to a simmer. Once it reaches a simmer, partially cover and turn back down to medium low and cook for 20 min. Add tomatoes and orzo, partially cover and let simmer for 7 min. Add chard and cover, cooking for 5 min more. Taste and adjust seasoning as necessary. Turn off heat and add lemon juice. Add 1/4 c parsley and 1/4 c cilantro. Serve, garnish with lemon wedge & harissa. 


Notes: To make vegetarian, sub vegetable broth for chicken broth and water.
